<item>
            <title>[LU-11447] How to isolate a target&apos;s RPCs to a specific NID?</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11447</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;See attached diag. &lt;span class=&quot;nobr&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/attachment/31108/31108_netconfig.pdf&quot; title=&quot;netconfig.pdf attached to LU-11447&quot;&gt;netconfig.pdf&lt;sup&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;rendericon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/link_attachment_7.gif&quot; height=&quot;7&quot; width=&quot;7&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;on a luster server that is running an MDT and OST targets. And if it has 2 NIDs on the same lnet network. Is there a way to isolate all MDT RPCs to ib0 and all OST RPCs to ib1?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The clients will only have a single interface.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
